HEADWORD: Embryology
<hw>Em`bry*ol"o*gy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>'e`mbryon</grk> an embryo + <ets>-logy</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>embryologie</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>The science which
relates to the formation and development of the embryo in animals and
plants; a study of the gradual development of the ovum until it reaches
the adult stage.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

